Text:
@crossfire6:  Actually, I appreciate not just A/V reviews but opinions on the movie(s), as well. That let me know it is probably not my cup of tea, since in addition to his scathing review, I never once saw a trailer for it, or heard anyone talk about it, or caught a review of it in a magazine or my local paper.

True, he was over-the-top with his review, but maybe it really is that bad of a film. After all, he felt compelled to put down on /paper/ what he thought to try and discourage us from seeing it, too, and by his own admission, he never commented before other than A/V quality.

Food for thought, anyway. Cheers.
